					<p>Sleep is something we take for granted till such time that we find ourselves being deprived of it. It is a fact that once in a while we always have our sleepless nights but it is something that cannot be borne on a regular basis. This can make you groggy the next day and leave you feeling drained all the time.</p>
<p>Here are a few tips to ensure a good snooze:</p>
<p><b>Physical activity:</b> It is a fact that the human body is a fine example of good engineering. This means to keep it running well you need to exercise regularly so that the body keeps in good shape. With the way our lives have shaped up we spend most part of our working days in front of the computer. This means the body does not feel as tired as it should and this affects our sleep patterns. Try and get in some form of physical activity of your choice to have good sleep.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.beautynstyle.net/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/Exercise.jpg"><img src="http://www.beautynstyle.net/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/Exercise.jpg" alt="Exercise" width="600" height="342" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-4019" /></a><br />
<b>Taking a shower:</b> Taking a lukewarm bath or shower at the end of a long day will help your muscles unwind and this will help you feel sleepy. The trick to taking a bath in the evening is getting the timing and the temperature right.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.beautynstyle.net/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/curtain.jpg"><img src="http://www.beautynstyle.net/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/curtain.jpg" alt="curtain" width="600" height="797" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-4018" /></a><br />
<b>Soothing fragrances:</b> Aromatherapy in the form of potpourri, candles or even a few drops of soothing scents like lavender on your pillow can help bring a sense of calm to your mind and let you sleep well.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.beautynstyle.net/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/fragrances.jpg"><img src="http://www.beautynstyle.net/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/fragrances.jpg" alt="fragrances" width="600" height="704" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-4020" /></a><br />
<b>Calm contemplation:</b> A few minutes of deep breathing along with a deliberate letting go off stuff that happened during the day is also another way to good sleep.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.beautynstyle.net/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/meditation.png"><img src="http://www.beautynstyle.net/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/meditation.png" alt="meditation" width="600" height="453" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-4021" /></a></p>
<p>These are some tips to guide you in general but if you feel your problem goes beyond these tips then you should consult a healthcare professional.</p>
